What is Git Stash?
Definition
Git Stash is a Git feature that temporarily saves your uncommitted changes so that you can work on something else without committing those changes.
Important commands:
•	Save changes: git stash stores all tracked modified files.
•	View all stashes: git stash list
•	Apply a stash: git stash apply – restores latest stash, stash remains in the stash list.
•	Apply a specific stash: git stash apply stash@{1}
•	Pop a stash: git stash pop
•	Drop a stash: git stash drop stash@{1}
•	Delete all stashes: git stash clear
•	Stash with a message: git stash push -m “Login feature”
•	Stash untracked files: git stash -u or git stash --include-untracked
•	Difference between stash apply and pop: 
Stash apply 				stash pop
Restores changes			Restore changes
Stash remains 				Removes the stash
Can be reused				cannot be reused

